Hi,

{color:#172b4d}I can’t find a way to change the background color behind the service desk announcement message. There is the possibility to customize the ‘Help center banner’ or ‘Banner background, link and button color’ but not the default pale blue for the Help Center announcement.{color}

{color:#172b4d}And an other related request, what is the way to change the hint text behind the help search form with the default text of ‘Find help and service’?{color}

{color:#172b4d}Link: [https://foo.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portals|https://ocfulfillment.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portals]{color}

{color:#172b4d}Regards{color}

{color:#172b4d}Michael{color}

When a Webhook event is triggered from Jira to Opsgenie for a JSM issue created, the payload sent to Opsgenie does not contain the Service Name, it only contains the Impacted Service ID.
This makes it difficult to configure rules in OG to route tickets to the right team based on the Impacted Service.

Example:

{code:java}
"customfield_10180": [
        {
          "id": "ari:cloud:graph::service/49daba40-0166-11eb-a63c-0a77f3f45304/6a2b9a6e-12a3-11eb-bb85-0a77f3f45304"
        }
      ],
{code}

The above is extracted from a payload, which contains the Service ID but not the Service name.
